SUMMARY:Frink Ridge - Invasive Plant Removal
DTSTAMP:20260406T013229Z
DTSTART:20260411T130000Z
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a restoration work party at Frink Park. \\nWe will 
	visit violence upon the invasive species at this job site\\\, removing hol
	ly\\\, ivy\\\, clematis\\\, and blackberry. Specifically\\\, we will compl
	ete a couple of survival rings\\\, freeing the trees of ivy that is depriv
	ing them of water and nutrients while adding significant weight to them\\\
	, risking them falling down in a wind storm. \\nI always invite those who 
	help clear areas in the spring to return in the fall to plant native plant
	s in the area they cleared. \\nRegister\n\nhttps://www.seattleparksfoundat
	ion.org/event/frink-ridge-invasive-plant-removal-2/\n\nFrom The Seattle Pa
